text=[[#excerpt]]%0aHomebrew is a neat whizzy package manager a la Fink and Macports, but using the great new tools of [[Git]] and [[Ruby]]. It will make your life so much easier.%0a[[#excerptend]]%0a%0a%0a%0a>>quote%3c%3c%0a(:nolinkwikiwords:)%0a! [[http://mxcl.github.com:80/ | Homebrew]]%0a%0a'''The missing package manager for OS X'''%0a%0a!! Homebrew installs the stuff you need that Apple didn't.%0a%0a(:source lang=bash:)%0a$ brew install wget%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0a!! Homebrew installs packages to their own directory and then symlinks their files into @@/usr/local@@.%0a%0a(:source lang=bash:)%0a$ cd /usr/local%0a$ find Cellar%0aCellar/wget/1.12%0aCellar/wget/1.12/bin/wget%0aCellar/wget/1.12/share/man/man1/wget.1%0a%0a$ ls -l bin%0abin/wget -> ../Cellar/wget/1.12/bin/wget%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0a%0a!! Homebrew won't install files outside its prefix, and you can place a Homebrew installation wherever you like.%0a%0a!! Trivially create your own Homebrew packages.%0a%0a(:source lang=bash:)%0a$ brew create http://foo.com/bar-1.0.tgz%0aCreated /usr/local/Library/Formula/bar.rb%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0a%0a!! It's all git and ruby underneath, so hack away with the knowledge that you can easily revert your modifications and merge upstream updates.%0a%0a(:source lang=bash:)%0a$ brew edit wget # opens in $EDITOR!%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0a!! Homebrew formula are simple Ruby scripts:%0a%0a(:source lang=ruby:)%0arequire 'formula'%0a%0aclass Wget %3c Formula%0a  homepage 'http://www.gnu.org/wget/'%0a  url 'http://ftp.gnu.org/wget-1.12.tar.gz'%0a  md5 '308a5476fc096a8a525d07279a6f6aa3'%0a%0a  def install%0a    system "./configure --prefix=#{prefix}"%0a    system 'make install'%0a  end%0aend%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0a!! Homebrew complements OS X. Install your gems with @@gem@@, and their dependencies with @@brew@@.%0a%0a!! Install Homebrew%0a%0a(:source lang=bash:)%0aruby -e "$(curl -fsSkL raw.github.com/mxcl/homebrew/go)"%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0aPaste that at a Terminal prompt.The script explains what it will do and then pauses before it does it. There are more installation options [[https://github.com/mxcl/homebrew/wiki/Installation | here]].%0a%0a!!Further Documentation:%0a%0a[[https://github.com/mxcl/homebrew/wiki | Homebrew Wiki]]%0a%0a(:linkwikiwords:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a>>comment%3c%3c%0aSummary: '''The missing package manager for OS X'''%0aTags: saved page, homebrew, brew, packages, package manager, tools, osx%0a(:tags-hide saved page, homebrew, brew, packages, package manager, tools, osx:)%0a(:title Homebrew &mdash; MacPorts driving you to drink? Try Homebrew!:)%0aSource: http://mxcl.github.com/homebrew/%0aParent: (Technology.)OSX%0aincludeme: [[Technology.OSX]]%0aCategories:[[!Articles]],[[!Links]],[[!Tools]]%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0aPage snagged at: Fri, 26 Oct 2012 17:02:47 -0500%0a
